## üéµ For Your Own Use

If you're building this project yourself, you are **free to download and use**
sound effects from Pixabay or other free sound libraries for your personal
Halloween skull project.

### Recommended Free Sound Libraries

1. **[Pixabay](https://pixabay.com/sound-effects/)** - Free for personal and
   commercial use

   - Search terms: "horror", "scary", "creepy", "halloween", "scream", "laugh"

2. **[Freesound.org](https://freesound.org/)** - CC-licensed sound effects

   - Requires attribution for some sounds

3. **[Zapsplat](https://www.zapsplat.com/)** - Free with attribution

   - Large collection of horror/Halloween sounds

4. **[BBC Sound Effects](https://sound-effects.bbcrewind.co.uk/)** - Free for
   personal use
   - High-quality professional recordings

### File Naming Convention

Files must follow the DFPlayer Mini naming convention:

```
03/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 001.mp3  (e.g., evil laugh)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 002.mp3  (e.g., scream)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 003.mp3  (e.g., creepy whisper)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ 004.mp3  (e.g., chains rattling)
```

**Format Requirements:**

- MP3 or WAV format
- Sample rate: 16kHz-48kHz recommended
- Bitrate: up to 320kbps
- Files numbered with 3 digits (001, 002, 003, etc.)

### Tips for Best Results

- Keep files short (2-10 seconds) for quick impact
- Normalize volume levels across all files
- Test on your actual speaker to ensure clarity
- Consider your skull's acoustic properties (muffled vs. clear)

---

**Note**: Always respect content licenses and terms of use when downloading
sound effects. If unsure, use content explicitly marked as "Public Domain" or
"CC0".
